Contributing Guidelines
=======================

Thank you for your interest in contributing to the DaVinci Project Server.
This document describes how to contribute code, documentation, or fixes.

Project License:
    This project is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3).
    All contributions must be compatible with this license.

How to Contribute
-----------------

1. Fork the repository on GitHub.
2. Create a new branch for your changes.
3. Make your modifications in a clear and organized manner.
4. Test your changes to ensure they do not break existing functionality.
5. Commit your changes with descriptive commit messages.
6. Submit a pull request to the main repository.

Coding Standards
----------------

- Use clear and readable code.
- Keep functions small and focused.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies.
- Document complex logic where appropriate.

Reporting Issues
----------------

If you find a bug or have a feature request, open an issue on GitHub with:

- A clear description of the problem
- Steps to reproduce (if applicable)
- Expected behavior
- Actual behavior

Security Issues
---------------

Do not report security vulnerabilities publicly.
Instead, contact the project maintainer directly.

End of File
-----------
